    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-20T19:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-20T19:50:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9746</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-20T20:50:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1918, 8.50 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2572. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 84. Legation’s 4244, August 8, your 115. Your views approved. You are
                    authorized proceed accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
